headline: Warren Confronts the Skeptics Who Fear Her Plans Go Too Far
abstract: In the early fall, Ms. Warren seemed to be the Democratic candidate to beat in Iowa. But many voters have had second thoughts over how her sweeping agenda would sell against President Trump.
lead_paragraph: MASON CITY, Iowa — Kristen Marttila’s alarm went off at 6 a.m. on Saturday and soon she was filling up two thermoses — one with hot water, one with soup — to gird for the day ahead: a two-hour drive to Mason City to campaign for Senator Elizabeth Warren in the icy cold.
